I wanted to drop a note and point out that Debian is available
over the local campus network via the CSUA.

For those familiar with debian, you can use something like
this in your /etc/apt/sources.list file:

deb http://linux.csua.berkeley.edu/debian/ stable main
deb-src http://linux.csua.berkeley.edu/debian/ stable main

Or, if you wanted to say, upgrade to 'woody' from 'potato'
you would add the following to your /etc/apt/sources.list:

deb http://linux.csua.berkeley.edu/debian/ testing main contrib non-free
deb-src http://linux.csua.berkeley.edu/debian/ testing main contrib non-free

This makes debian a very quick install over the net here.

- Colby


